        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-06-21T14:00:13Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workforce Investment Disclosure Act of 2023 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill requires publicly traded companies to disclose information annually regarding workforce management policies, practices, and performance. This includes&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;demographic information;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;data on temporary and contract workers;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;employee turnover rate;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;employee skills and capabilities;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;workforce health, safety, and well-being, including findings of harassment or discrimination; and&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;employee compensation, benefits, and incentives.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Securities and Exchange Commission may exempt emerging growth companies from certain disclosures. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
